<title>CANADA: CAE Inc to get C$32 mln govt loan-newspaper.</title>
<headline>CAE Inc to get C$32 mln govt loan-newspaper.</headline>
<dateline>MONTREAL 1997-03-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>CAE Inc is set to receive a C$32 million interest-free loan next week under the Canadian government's Technology Partnerships program, Toronto's Globe and Mail newspaper reported on Saturday.</p>
<p>The Globe report said CAE will receive the money to create a new generation of software to develop real-time computer-generated images of such things as topographies and runways for use in the aerospace company's flight simulators.</p>
<p>The loan is part of a C$100 million project, called &quot;Vistech,&quot; which is expected to create 200 jobs at CAE's facilities in St. Laurent, Quebec, the newspaper said.</p>
<p>Canada's Industry Minister John Manley will announce the contribution next week, the Globe and Mail reported.</p>
<p>No one was immediately available at the company for comment on the newspaper story.</p>
<p>((Reuters Toronto Bureau 416 941-8100))</p>
